<1ST_LINE>r a AM-NYLottery     12-04 0316</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-NY Lottery,0326</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>12 Winners In Record $45 Million New York Lottery</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twelve lottery tickets bear the magic numbers
entitling the holders to a share of a record $45 million-plus
jackpot so enticing that an estimated eight out of 10 New York
adults tried their luck, officials said Sunday.
   The holders of the $1 Lotto tickets beat odds of nearly 13
million to 1 in winning the jackpot, the biggest in the 12-year
history of the state lottery.
   The jackpot could go higher, when sales are finally tabulated,
said lottery spokesman George Yamin.
   Each ticket was worth $3.75 million, meaning each ticket holder
will receive $142,857 after taxes each year for the next 20 years.
The jackpot could be claimed immediately at lottery offices, which
were specially opened Sunday.
   Acting Lottery Director Russell Gladieux said 37.4 million
tickets sold in the frenzy leading up to Saturday night's drawing,
going at about 28,000 a minute.
   ``Our best estimate, based on past studies, is that when we get a
jackpot this high, 80 percent of (adult) New York residents play,''
said Gladieux.
   The winning tickets all were bought in the New York metropolitan
area. ``I don't know how I'm going to explain that to the upstate
press,'' Gladieux said.
   The jackpot rose from $26 million after no one won Wednesday's
drawing.
   The biggest previous jackpot awarded in New York was $41 million
in 1985, divided among three tickets, one held by 21 factory
workers. The largest single winner in New York took received a $30.5
million jackpot in 1986.
   The world's biggest lottery jackpot, $61.98 million, was divided
among three winning tickets in California in October. The largest
single winner in history was a Florida woman who claimed $55.16
million in September.
   The winning numbers Saturday in New York's Lotto game were: 1, 8,
13, 18, 28, 48. The supplemental number was 19.
</TEXT>
