<HEAD>British Embassy Reopens In Terhan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Union Jack flew over the British
Embassy in Tehran on Sunday after an eight-year absence, the
official Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
   The British flag was raised in a ceremony marking the return of
British diplomats to the building after full diplomatic relations
between Iran and Britain were restored last month.
   Swedish diplomats had looked after British interests in Iran
since the embassy was closed after the Iranian takeover of the U.S.
Embassy in 1979.
   Relations were all but ruptured last year when an Iranian
diplomat was arrested in Britain on shoplifting charges and a
British envoy in Tehran was detained.
   IRNA, monitored in Nicosia, quoted Charge d'Affairs Gordon Pirie
as saying the two countries will exchange ambassadors next year.
